":"The neurological exam shows weakness in hand grip, finger abduction, and adduction, along with decreased sensation over the fifth finger and the lateral aspect of the fourth finger.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052929,0.094988,0.10984,0.12516,0.11559,0.10872,0.099515,0.085446,0.068876,0.0546,0.04632,0.038015],"unified_progress":[0.05703,0.094045,0.10402,0.10972,0.10829,0.099611,0.091776,0.084229,0.092642,0.063098,0.052223,0.04331]},{"section":6,"text":"Hmm, the key here is the distribution of the symptoms.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.068314,0.1165,0.10402,0.11119,0.089071,0.081996,0.084559,0.072803,0.069787,0.079279,0.067979,0.054499],"unified_progress":[0.043516,0.080832,0.091973,0.1042,0.10073,0.092746,0.094868,0.089205,0.084209,0.089179,0.070138,0.058405]},{"section":7,"text":"The numbness and weakness are localized to the fourth and fifth fingers.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.068924,0.10024,0.09616,0.098522,0.088309,0.085822,0.084463,0.080266,0.076215,0.07353,0.07405,0.073499],"unified_progress":[0.06338,0.085079,0.086301,0.090631,0.089815,0.091677,0.088372,0.089499,0.085389,0.080945,0.076772,0.072139]},{"section":8,"text":"I remember that the radial nerve is responsible for the innervation of the thumb and the lateral side of the index finger, but wait, that's not exactly the area mentioned here.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046966,0.07445,0.083033,0.093078,0.095926,0.097554,0.099023,0.096524,0.092605,0.085929,0.073546,0.061365],"unified_progress":[0.03782,0.065787,0.087756,0.096312,0.099646,0.10588,0.10141,0.096606,0.092304,0.089313,0.071774,0.055383]},{"section":9,"text":"The fifth finger is the little finger, and the fourth is the ring finger.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04323,0.065368,0.078633,0.088857,0.096189,0.10041,0.10199,0.10114,0.096808,0.08782,0.076178,0.063382],"unified_progress":[0.041148,0.066479,0.082941,0.094166,0.098936,0.10373,0.10087,0.098347,0.094052,0.087681,0.073152,0.058507]},{"section":10,"text":"So maybe it's not the radial nerve.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050079,0.069835,0.078775,0.086683,0.089758,0.092802,0.096275,0.09573,0.094716,0.094332,0.084162,0.066852],"unified_progress":[0.04434,0.067125,0.080612,0.091346,0.095659,0.096507,0.097782,0.097097,0.094194,0.093164,0.079219,0.062956]},{"section":11,"text":"Wait, the median nerve is more involved with the fingers on the palmar side.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040722,0.067149,0.077484,0.086852,0.093395,0.097735,0.10129,0.10116,0.098959,0.093207,0.079709,0.062339],"unified_progress":[0.035652,0.065029,0.08354,0.095883,0.0998,0.10419,0.10304,0.099193,0.094675,0.090531,0.07322,0.055252]},{"section":12,"text":"The median nerve supplies the palmar aspect of the hand, including the third, fourth, and fifth fingers.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031849,0.054442,0.070916,0.084123,0.097691,0.10529,0.10873,0.11062,0.1058,0.092006,0.075528,0.063002],"unified_progress":[0.032111,0.059992,0.081471,0.095481,0.10157,0.11177,0.10649,0.10236,0.0965,0.088562,0.070056,0.053642]},{"section":13,"text":"But the patient's symptoms are on the fourth and fifth fingers, specifically the lateral aspect of the fourth and the fifth.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049294,0.067185,0.074792,0.083335,0.089062,0.09441,0.097745,0.098554,0.096653,0.09032,0.084116,0.074534],"unified_progress":[0.04907,0.070932,0.081448,0.090038,0.094565,0.097821,0.096391,0.096196,0.093086,0.086699,0.07742,0.066334]},{"section":14,"text":"That makes me think about the ulnar nerve because the ulnar nerve runs along the medial side of the hand and controls the fifth finger and the lateral side of the fourth finger.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":fa