ccident, which could mean he sustained a fracture in the elbow.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048091,0.089543,0.095067,0.090618,0.087462,0.087127,0.089875,0.088722,0.087924,0.089341,0.078752,0.067478],"unified_progress":[0.08348,0.11019,0.093949,0.086544,0.084724,0.085747,0.082109,0.087189,0.080148,0.075231,0.069531,0.061156]},{"section":20,"text":"The fracture might have caused a lesion in the ulnar nerve, leading to these symptoms.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053046,0.067388,0.082061,0.08787,0.092185,0.094241,0.095923,0.094981,0.091627,0.088302,0.079027,0.07335],"unified_progress":[0.062873,0.081961,0.091789,0.09465,0.092336,0.094819,0.090685,0.090407,0.085878,0.079169,0.071546,0.063887]},{"section":21,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis here is an ulnar nerve injury, possibly due to the elbow fracture.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025944,0.050415,0.067081,0.077273,0.079702,0.082312,0.087782,0.089743,0.091952,0.10521,0.10818,0.13441],"unified_progress":[0.029487,0.056745,0.07106,0.082348,0.082313,0.086318,0.089383,0.091854,0.093941,0.094415,0.10473,0.1174]},{"section":22,"text":"The patient's symptoms of numbness and weakness in the fourth and fifth fingers, along with the neurological findings, point towards an injury involving the ulnar nerve.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022044,0.035879,0.040387,0.045149,0.048454,0.054487,0.061329,0.074658,0.089648,0.11401,0.15957,0.25439],"unified_progress":[0.022473,0.033861,0.038724,0.047144,0.051143,0.066119,0.067995,0.082587,0.096711,0.10743,0.15479,0.23102]},{"section":23,"text":"The ulnar nerve is responsible for sensation in these areas and contributes to hand grip strength.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022949,0.032789,0.044562,0.054347,0.067006,0.07744,0.087008,0.098775,0.10972,0.11522,0.12641,0.16377],"unified_progress":[0.022657