46,0.02933]},{"section":4,"text":"The neurological findings show weakness in handgrip, finger abduction and adduction, and decreased sensation over the fifth finger and the lateral aspect of the fourth finger.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.065009,0.10807,0.11562,0.10454,0.10522,0.095206,0.088987,0.078558,0.070069,0.059528,0.056595,0.052597],"unified_progress":[0.069465,0.107,0.11071,0.11171,0.10596,0.098925,0.087521,0.081268,0.079903,0.05897,0.048958,0.039601]},{"section":5,"text":"First, I need to think about the anatomy of the elbow and how fractures can affect the nerves.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050199,0.072032,0.08986,0.09237,0.099058,0.097903,0.089972,0.088133,0.081869,0.093627,0.076402,0.068577],"unified_progress":[0.040809,0.076648,0.088935,0.10249,0.10158,0.094835,0.09689,0.09095,0.086826,0.091376,0.072001,0.056653]},{"section":6,"text":"The elbow has several nerves passing through it, including the radial, ulnar, and median nerves.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040324,0.069009,0.087906,0.099765,0.10436,0.10288,0.10346,0.095269,0.088706,0.078786,0.069493,0.060047],"unified_progress":[0.038193,0.071486,0.091192,0.11611,0.10806,0.10315,0.099422,0.091868,0.090239,0.075255,0.061471,0.053561]},{"section":7,"text":"The radial nerve is responsible for the sensory innervation of the back of the hand and some motor functions, the median nerve handles the thumb and first two fingers, and the ulnar nerve is responsible for the fourth and fifth fingers.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039029,0.066031,0.0847,0.097797,0.10408,0.1041,0.10534,0.09824,0.091467,0.079472,0.069721,0.060023],"unified_progress":[0.03737,0.070465,0.090851,0.10554,0.11146,0.1072,0.10335,0.094756,0.093588,0.075527,0.060473,0.049431]},{"section":8,"text":"Given the symptoms, the numbness and weakness are in the fourth and fifth fingers.","dimension":1